8 EQUAL PAY FOR EQUAL WORK
9 SECTION 1.2.(a) Chapter 95 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
10 Article to read:
11 "Article 2B.
12 "Equal Pay Act.
13 "§ 95-25.26. Definitions.
14 The following definitions apply in this Article:
15 (1) Employee. – Every person in receipt of or entitled to compensation for labor
16 performed for another.
17 (2) Employer. – Includes (i) this State and any local political subdivision of the
18 State and (ii) every person having control or direction of any person employed
19 at any labor, or responsible directly or indirectly for the wages of another, who
20 employs more than five employees.
21 (3) Person. – As defined by G.S. 95-25.2(11).
22 (4) Wage or wages. – Any compensation for labor measured by time, piece, or
23 otherwise.
24 "§ 95-25.27. Equal wage rates.
25 (a) No employer may pay any person in the employer's employ at wage rates less than
26 the rates paid to employees of the opposite sex in the same establishment for the same quantity
27 and quality of the same classification of work. Any employer who violates this section is liable
28 to the employee affected in the amount of the wages that the employee is deprived by reason of
29 the violation.
30 (b) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (a) of this section, nothing in this
31 section prohibits a variation of rates of pay for employees engaged in the same classification of
32 work based upon seniority, a difference in length of service, ability, skill, difference in duties or
33 services performed, whether regularly or occasionally, difference in the shift or time of day
34 worked, hours of work, or restrictions or prohibitions on lifting or moving objects in excess of
35 specified weight, or other reasonable differentiation, or factor or factors other than sex, when
36 exercised in good faith.
37 (c) An employer that is in violation of this section may not reduce the pay of any
38 employee in order to bring the employer into compliance with this Article.
39 (d) An employer shall not retaliate against any employee who seeks redress pursuant to
40 this Article or who participates in the investigation of a complaint under this Article.
41 "§ 95-25.28. Complaints; enforcement; civil actions.
42 (a) An affected employee may file with the Department of Labor a complaint that the
43 wages paid to the employee are less than the wages to which the employee is entitled under this
44 Article. The Department of Labor shall investigate the complaint and notify the employer and
45 employee of the results of the investigation.
46 (b) An employee receiving less than the wage to which the employee is entitled under
47 this section may recover in a civil action the balance of such wages, together with the costs and
48 attorneys' fees, notwithstanding any agreement to work for a lesser wage. The employee is not
49 required to exhaust administrative remedies before filing the civil action.
50 (c) A civil action pursuant to this section shall be instituted within two years after the
51 date that the alleged violation is discovered by the affected employee."
