3 HEALTHY FAMILIES & WORKPLACES/REQUIRE PAID LEAVE/WORKPLACE
4 HEAT SAFETY PROTECTIONS
5 SECTION 1.3.(a) Chapter 95 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
6 Article to read:
7 "Article 3A.
8 "Healthy Families and Healthy Workplaces Act.
9 "§ 95-31.1. Short title and legislative purpose.
10 (a) This Article shall be known and may be cited as the "Healthy Families and Healthy
11 Workplaces Act."
12 (b) The public policy of this State is declared as follows: The health and safety needs of
13 employees and their families and the protection of employees from losing their jobs and pay
14 while they seek medical care for themselves and their family members are subjects of concern
15 requiring legislation to promote the general welfare of the people of the State without
16 jeopardizing the competitive position of North Carolina business and industry. The General
17 Assembly declares that the general welfare of the State requires the enactment of this law under
18 the police power of the State.
19 "§ 95-31.2. Definitions.
20 (a) The following definitions apply in this Article:
21 (1) Child. – A biological, adopted, or foster child, stepchild, legal ward, or child
22 of a parent standing in loco parentis.
23 (2) Domestic violence. – As defined in G.S. 50B-1.
24 (3) Employ. – As defined by G.S. 95-25.2(3).
25 (4) Employee. – As defined by G.S. 95-25.2(4).
26 (5) Employer. – As defined by G.S. 95-25.2(5).
27 (6) Health care provider. –
28 a. A doctor of medicine or osteopathy licensed to practice medicine
29 under federal law, any state law, or the laws of another country
30 wherein the person practices.
31 b. A physician assistant licensed in this State licensed to practice under
32 federal law, any state law, or the laws of another country wherein the
33 person practices.
34 c. A family nurse practitioner or certified nurse midwife licensed to
35 practice under federal law, any state law, or the laws of another
36 country wherein the person practices.
37 (7) Immediate family member. – A child, grandchild, sibling, spouse, domestic
38 partner, civil union partner, parent, or grandparent of an employee, or a
39 spouse, domestic partner, or civil union partner of a parent or grandparent of
40 the employee, or a sibling of a spouse, domestic partner, or civil union partner
41 of the employee, or any other individual related by blood to the employee or
42 whose close association with the employee is the equivalent of a family
43 relationship.
44 (8) Paid sick time or paid sick days. – Time that is (i) compensated at the same
45 hourly rate and with the same benefits, including health care benefits, as the
46 employee normally earns during hours worked and (ii) provided by an
47 employer to an employee for the purposes described in G.S. 95-31.4(b) of this
48 Article.
49 (9) Parent. – A biological, foster, step, or adoptive parent of an employee or an
50 employee's spouse, or other person who stood in loco parentis during the
51 childhood of an employee or employee's spouse.
